  "texts": [
    "Combining a model that was already \"jailbroken\" using a specific jailbreak prompt (JBP) at training with the same JBP at inference consistently leads to higher attack success rates than applying a different JBP.",
    "For instance, 81.2% > 12.2% (for the anti-poisoned model) and 22.4% > 14.0% (for the hypo-poisoned model).",
    "• OCR-based attacks.",
    "The same phenomenon holds when the same JBP is applied via OCR at inference time.",
    "That is, a model poisoned with a particular JBP becomes more susceptible when confronted with the matching JBP embedded in an image, compared to a different JBP."
  ],
